Metatibia about 1.5 times as long as metafemur, slightly curved and thinner proximally, markedly swollen medially. Apical tibial spurs small. Male abdominal terminalia: 8th sternite long, unspecialized; 9th tergite narrow, extending laterally almost to 9th sternite; 9th sternite long and rather narrow (boat-like), extending caudally to level of outer margin of ectoproct; ectoproct in general rounded, appears slightly concave ventrally (poorly visible), with long setae and large rounded callus cerci (
Fig. 6
); outer, ventral margins of ectoproct without visible processes.

Etymology. From the Latin parvus [- a , - um ] (comparative
minor
), small (smaller), in reference to its smaller size compared to other species of the genus.
